@page "/quick-start"
<PageTitle>Quick Start - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="quick-start">Quick Start</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="steps">Steps</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                Get a Saascade-powered Blazor app running in three steps.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                Install the NuGet package, register your chosen design system in Program.cs,
                and add the using directive to _Imports.razor. After that, all Saascade
                components are available across your entire application.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="first-component">Your First Component</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                Once the library is installed and the design system is registered, you can use
                any Saascade component directly in any Razor page or component.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <pre><code>&lt;Card&gt;
    &lt;CardTitle&gt;Hello, Saascade&lt;/CardTitle&gt;
    &lt;CardBody&gt;
        &lt;P&gt;Your first design-system-aware card.&lt;/P&gt;
        &lt;Button Specialization="btn-primary"&gt;Get Started&lt;/Button&gt;
    &lt;/CardBody&gt;
&lt;/Card&gt;</code></pre>

            <p>
                The CSS classes applied to each element depend entirely on the active design system.
                Switching frameworks requires only changing the registration in Program.cs.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="quickstart-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Quick Start</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Quick Start</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                Register VanillaBootstrap5 in Program.cs and include DesignSystemStylesheetReferences
                in your layout. The Card above will render with Bootstrap's card and card-body classes,
                the Button will receive btn and the specialization value you pass. Bootstrap's CDN
                stylesheet loads automatically — no additional configuration is required.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="quickstart-daisyui">DaisyUI Quick Start</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Quick Start</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                Register DaisyUI in Program.cs and include DesignSystemStylesheetReferences in
                your layout. The same Card markup will render with DaisyUI's semantic classes and
                default theme tokens. You can change the active DaisyUI theme by setting the
                data-theme attribute on the html element — all Saascade components update
                automatically since they rely on DaisyUI's CSS variables.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="quickstart-basecoat">Basecoat Quick Start</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Quick Start</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                Register Basecoat in Program.cs and include DesignSystemStylesheetReferences in
                your layout. The same Card markup will render with Basecoat's utility-first Tailwind
                class composition. Basecoat gives you a minimal starting point that you can extend
                with additional Tailwind utilities through the Class or Specialization parameters
                without modifying the component itself.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("quick-start", "Quick Start"),
    new TocItem("steps", "Steps", 2),
    new TocItem("first-component", "Your First Component", 2),
    new TocItem("quickstart-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5 Quick Start", 2),
    new TocItem("quickstart-daisyui", "DaisyUI Quick Start", 2),
    new TocItem("quickstart-basecoat", "Basecoat Quick Start", 2)
])" />

</div>
